<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Wilson</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-24"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Wilson advises the department that he is in receipt of a note
                                from the foreign office giving information that the Belgian
                                Government <pb facs="1265" n="1115" xml:id="pg_1115"/> “does not
                                offer any objections to the Russian proposition concerning the
                                adhesion of nonsignatory powers to the convention of 1899, if this
                                proposition receives the assent of all the signatory powers which is
                                required by article 60 of the said convention.”)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>